This paper is primarily focused on the optimization and training of deep neural networks (DNNs), which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of batch normalization (BN) in DNNs, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of residual networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the conditioning of the optimization problem, which is a topic in numerical optimization (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
